    {
      "name": "Plan to Get Paid",
      "description": "When your team has at least one Pyro, Hydro, Electro, or Cryo character, the Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robots from the Elemental Burst Hidden Aces: Seven Tools of the Hunter will be enhanced based on the number of characters of each corresponding element.\nJahoda secretly keeps track of these characters. Among them, the element with the highest number of characters determines the enhancement effect:\n· Pyro: Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robots deal 130% of their original DMG.\n· Hydro: Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robots heal for 120% of their original healing amount.\n· Electro: The number of Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robots increases by one.\n· Cryo: The attack interval of Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robots is reduced by 10%.\n\nIf there's a tie between elements, the order of priority that determines which enhancement takes effect is: Pyro, Hydro, Electro, then Cryo. Only one elemental effect can initially be triggered.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_05.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sweet Berry Bounty",
      "description": "When a Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robot from the Elemental Burst Hidden Aces: Seven Tools of the Hunter triggers healing on an active team member, if that character's HP is above 70%, their Elemental Mastery will be increased by 100 for 6s.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_06.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Moonsign Benediction: Rooftop Dash",
      "description": "When Jahoda is in the party, the party's Moonsign will increase by 1 level.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_07.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Backstreet Guile",
      "description": "When dispatched on an expedition in Nod-Krai, time consumed is reduced by 25%.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_08.png"
    }
  ],
  "constellations": [
    {
      "name": "One More Flask!",
      "description": "When a Fluffy Meowball fired by the Purr-loined Treasure Flask from the Elemental Skill Savvy Strategy: Splitting the Spoils hits an enemy, there is a 50% chance for it to bounce, dealing the corresponding Elemental DMG to nearby opponents.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_03.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Rogue's Quick Thinking",
      "description": "Moonsign: Ascendant Gleam: In the Ascension Talent \"Plan to Get Paid,\" Jahoda can secretly track, in addition to the element with the highest number of characters, the element with the next highest number of characters among the remaining types. This allows up to two elemental effects to be active at once. You must first unlock the Ascension Talent \"Plan to Get Paid.\"",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_02.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Desperate Gamble",
      "description": "Increases the Level of Hidden Aces: Seven Tools of the Hunter by 3.\nMaximum upgrade level is 15.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_U_Jahoda_01.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "Wild Berry Amid the Dust",
      "description": "When a Purrsonal Coordinated Assistance Robot from the Elemental Burst Hidden Aces: Seven Tools of the Hunter undergoes an Elemental Conversion, Jahoda will recover 4 Elemental Energy.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_S_Jahoda_01.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "The Greatest Treasure",
      "description": "Increases the Level of Savvy Strategy: Splitting the Spoils by 3.\nMaximum upgrade level is 15.",
      "icon": "https://gi.yatta.moe/assets/UI/UI_Talent_U_Jahoda_02.png"
    },
    {
      "name": "The Littlest Luck",
      "description": "Moonsign: Ascendant Gleam: After the Purr-loined Treasure Flask from the Elemental Skill Savvy Strategy: Splitting the Spoils is full, nearby Moonsign characters in your party have their CRIT Rate increased by 5% and CRIT DMG increased by 40% for 20s.",
